    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-04-01T17:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-04-01T17:40:00-05:00" n="74"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d74">
                <head>74. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Vietnam</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d74fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>(US) <gloss target="#t_S1"
                            >S</gloss> VIET Secret; Operational Immediate; Limit Distribution.
                        Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_HTJ1">Heavner</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_SWG1">Stoneman</persName> and cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_WCB1">Wood</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_REE1"
                            >Rice</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_HR1">Hilsman</persName>, and
                        in <gloss target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_ISA1">ISA</gloss>
                        in substance by <persName corresp="#p_HRALC1">Heinz</persName>. Repeated to
                            <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> for <gloss
                            target="#t_POLAD1">POLAD</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1963-04-01T17:40:00-05:00">April 1, 1963, 5:40 p.m.</date>
                        </hi>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>910. State/<gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>/Defense message. <gloss
                        target="#t_EMBTEL1">Embtel</gloss> 860.<note n="2" xml:id="d74fn2">
                        <ref target="#d70">Document 70</ref>.</note> Concur with your plan tell
                        <persName corresp="#p_NHU1">Nhu</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_DIEM1"
                        >Diem</persName> further procurement and shipment hamlet kit materials,
                        <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss>-480 and <gloss target="#t_AID1"
                        >AID</gloss> dollar procurement items for hamlets not justified unless there
                    adequate piaster fund and agreed procedures for piaster use.</p>
                <p>You may further wish indicate that new approvals are currently pending in <gloss
                        target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>/W for additional funds for direct
                    counter-insurgency procurement and for additional Title II <gloss
                        target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss>-480 commodities. We may hold up these approvals
                    pending resolution piaster issue. <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>, we will
                    continue processing papers assuming satisfactory outcome your negotiations End
                        <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
